		<td><b>Are pure primary colors ever useful in a color ramp?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It seems like trying to fit a perfect 255,0,0 red, or 255,255,0 yellow into a smooth color ramp, is well, a lot harder than it looks.  Is it possible to make a ramp that does not look uneven?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
