	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">psycopathicteen wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">It seems like trying to fit a perfect 255,0,0 red, or 255,255,0 yellow into a smooth color ramp, is well, a lot harder than it looks.  Is it possible to make a ramp that does not look uneven?</div><br /><br />Sure they can! Primary colors can be used as a nice ramp between separate color ranges.<br />At least, that's what I've used them for.<br /><br />(...I can't seem to find the palette I had figured out, from 2 years ago. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_neutral.gif" alt=":|" title="Neutral" />)<br /><br />If you're serious about figuring things out, try for all 4 primaries: red, blue, green, yellow.

		

		</td>
