	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I just remembered something.  My LCD screen looks different depending on the angle, so that could be the reason why pure primary colors tend to pop out too much.  If I make them look good at one angle, they would look disjointed at other viewing angles.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


