	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Are pure primary colors ever useful in a color ramp?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />We could build a laser SDTV without <em>too</em> much difficulty. Modulating red and blue solid-state laser diodes at the required ≈3MHz bandwidth is pretty easy; I'm not certain whether the nonlinear optics used by green solid-state lasers pose a problem or not.<br /><br />The horizontal deflection is the only particularly hard part, and I think a high-precision many-sided front-surface mirrored polygonal prism should be workable there.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


